Math.Equation

Class EquationSystem

  • java.lang.Object
    • Math.Equation.EquationSystem
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable, Math.MathObject

    public class EquationSystem
extends java.lang.Object
implements Math.MathObject, java.lang.Iterable
    The main class for all equation-related things. It keeps track of different equations, and of names of CustomFunctions (and the corresponding classes for them).
    Since:
    0.1

    • Field Detail

      • equations

        protected java.util.ArrayList<Equation> equations
        An ArrayList of all Equations that are related to this class. The "main" Equation is the first one in the list. All others should be related to them.
        Note: This is also where variables are defined. To define x = 4 * 3, you would do add(new Equation().add("x","4 * 3")).

      • functions

        protected java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,CustomFunction> functions
        A HashMap of all CustomFunctions. The key is the user-defined name of it, and the value is the CustomFunction associated with it.
        Note: that a user-defined name could be the name of the file that defines the CustomFunction, or another name. For example, a CustomFunction with a name of "graphEq" might have a key of "displayEq" instead.

      • functions

        public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,CustomFunction> functions()
        Returns functions. functions is a HashMap with the String as the key, and CustomFunction.
        Note: The key is what should be used when defining equations.
        Example: functions might be defined as (pseudocode) functions = {"fac", CustomFunction("factorial")}. The class "factorial" is linked to "fac", so
        y = fac(x) would work, but y = factorial(x) wouldn't.
        Returns:
        This class's functions.

      • equations

        public java.util.ArrayList<Equation> equations()
        Returns equations. Each Equation in equations _should_ (but doesn't have to be) related somehow to this class. Note that this is also where different variables are defined ({"x","5"} means x = 5).
        Returns:
        This class's equations.

        public EquationSystem isolate(java.lang.String toIso)
